==English==

===Etymology===
From the classical Greek transliterated as "diabainein," meaning "to pass through," it is from the participle of this verb, and therefore means passing through.&nbsp; This refers to the excessive amounts of urine produced by sufferers.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A disease which is attended with a persistent, excessive discharge of urine.&nbsp; Most frequently the urine is not only increased in quantity, but contains saccharine matter.&nbsp; Untreated, the disease leads to an earlier death.   

